<TITLE> Educationist Dr Reza dead at 64 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 21 (bdnews24.com)  The Independent editor and former caretaker government adviser Mahbubul Alam's brother and educationist Dr Sadrel Amin Latifur Reza Friday died of cardiac arrest in Almati, Kazakhstan. Arrangements were being made to bring his body to Dhaka, Mahbubul Alam said in a faxed message. Dr Reza taught economics at the University of Kazakhstan at the time of his death. He was 64. He left behind two daughters, brothers and sisters and friends and well wishers to mourn him. Dr Reza began his career as a fellow of Pakistan Institute of Development Studies in Karachi. He headed the Department of Economics of Dhaka University. He was also director general of the Bangladesh Institute of Development Studies. Dr Reza also held the position of a senior fellow of the Asian Development Bank (ADB) Research Institute in Tokyo. He joined as professor of the Department of Economics at the University of Kazakhstan last year. Prior to the new job, he was professor of economics in the Independent University of Bangladesh. He authored books and many research papers. Dr Reza got first class got first class in masters in economics from Dhaka University and also did masters from the University of Manchester, UK. He did his PhD in development economics from the UK. bdne
